comment:
* File information returned by {@link Os#fstat}, {@link Os#lstat}, and {@link Os#stat}.
 * Corresponds to C's {@code struct stat} from {@code <stat.h>}.

variables.name: st_dev
variables.comment: Device ID of device containing file.

variables.name: st_nlink
variables.comment: Number of hard links to the file.

variables.name: st_rdev
variables.comment: Device ID (if file is character or block special).

variables.name: st_size
variables.comment:
* For regular files, the file size in bytes.
     * For symbolic links, the length in bytes of the pathname contained in the symbolic link.
     * For a shared memory object, the length in bytes.
     * For a typed memory object, the length in bytes.
     * For other file types, the use of this field is unspecified.

variables.name: st_atime
variables.comment: Seconds part of time of last access.

variables.name: st_atim
variables.comment: StructTimespec with time of last access.

variables.name: st_mtime
variables.comment: Seconds part of time of last data modification.

variables.name: st_mtim
variables.comment: StructTimespec with time of last modification.

variables.name: st_ctime
variables.comment: Seconds part of time of last status change

variables.name: st_ctim
variables.comment: StructTimespec with time of last status change.

variables.name: st_blksize
variables.comment:
* A file system-specific preferred I/O block size for this object.
     * For some file system types, this may vary from file to file.

variables.name: st_blocks
variables.comment: Number of blocks allocated for this object.
